ce:section.ce:para:
To explore the AIE property of APPTEPP, UV-vis absorption and fluorescence emission spectra of APPTEPP in DMF/water media was recorded (Fig. 1
                        ). Concentrations of APPTEPP were kept at 1.0 × 10−6 mol L−1. The luminogen start to aggregate when water fractions exceed 20% with slightly decreasing absorbance intensity. The maximum absorption peak nearly stayed in the same position at 380 nm and the level-off tail suggested the formation of aggregates [54,55]. Also, the DLS data (Fig. 2
                        a) of the solution APPTPEP (DMF/H2O = 1: 99), revealed the formation of aggregates with average hydrodynamic diameter of 102 nm (polydispersity index = 0.312). APPTPEP is non-fluorescent in DMF with very low quantum yield of 0.4%. With the addition of water, the fluorescence intensity increased gradually and significantly enhanced when the water faction is up to 99%, which is about 60-fold enhancement than that in pure DMF (Fig. 1b). These results showed a typical AIE activity that the non-radiative processes were restrained because of the restriction of intramolecular rotation and intermolecular interaction [56–58].
